comments: I tried seeing the pattern in the words for each shape first and then for each color and I realized quickly which ones we're buvi, zeti, gafi, wopi and then the endings which were -sha for yellow, -se for blue, -xo for red, -thu for gray. It was quite easy to remember the shapes because the words somehow resembled those shapes? I don't know how to explain. Same for colors more or less. I did find some trouble with the audio, though, at the start and during the study, some words sounded very similar to others so I couldn't have written the right ones if I didn't recall them, just by hearing them. What was hard is that at first I got the photos and words randomly and had to figure out the pattern myself and didn't have it explained or laid out by color and shape.
